From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 2026 21:19:38 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] audio: cix: sky1: enable HDMI/DisplayPort audio output under
 ACPI

Wire up the complete HDMI/DP audio pipeline for ACPI boot on Sky1.
Five I2S multi-channel controllers (I2S5-I2S9) feed audio to five
DisplayPort transmitters via the audio subsystem DMA-350 engine.

The audio subsystem requires coordinated bring-up of several
components that have no ACPI _DEP-style ordering:

  clk-sky1-audss: Transition ACPI power resource to D0, powering
  on the audio subsystem (RCSU PD_CTRL, memory repair).  Register
  clkdev entries from CLKA table for all audio consumers.

  reset-sky1-audss: Register reset_control_lookup entries so DMA
  and HDA controllers can find their reset lines without DT
  phandles.

  arm-dma350: Defer probe until clock and reset controllers are
  available.  Register as ACPI DMA controller so I2S consumers
  can resolve FixedDMA resources to DMA channels.

  cdns_i2s_mc: Provide explicit DMA channel names in PCM config
  so channels are requested via ACPI at PCM creation time (the
  generic dmaengine-pcm code only pre-allocates for DT devices).

  trilin_dptx: Set no_i2s_capture on HDMI codec registration
  since DP ports have no Audio Return Channel.

  sky1-card: Add ACPI device table (CIXH6070) for auto-loading.
  Add cix_card_parse_acpi() to build fixed DAI link topology
  mapping I2S5-I2S9 to hdmi-audio-codec.0-4 with jack detection.

  DTS: Rename sound card model to "cix_sky1" matching the ALSA
  UCM2 configuration directory for consistent card naming.

Tested on Radxa Orion O6: all five HDMI/DP outputs appear in
PipeWire/GNOME with working jack detection for connected displays.
